## 3. WHY THIS MATTERS FOR THE SCHEMA

Everything above is **`frame.external_standard` + `frame.external_control` + `frame.crosswalk`**. The tables already exist. What's missing is the actual control text, which is thousands of rows and mostly copyrighted — NIST and GAO are public domain, ISO and PCI and COSO are licensed and I can't reproduce them.

That has a design consequence worth stating: for licensed frameworks, you store the **reference** (`ISO-27001:A.5.1`) and your own crosswalk rationale, not the control text. The text stays in your licensed copy. This is normal GRC-tool practice and it's why every commercial GRC platform makes you upload your own ISO standard.

